# Copy these into your Railway BACKEND service → Variables.
# Do NOT commit real passwords to Git.
#
# Prefer "Add Reference" → MySQL service (private network, no egress fees).
# Do NOT use the public proxy URL unless you are connecting from outside Railway.
#
# --- Option A (recommended): reference MySQL service variables ---
#
# SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL (build via Railway "Add Reference" for each ${{...}} token)
#   Private network (recommended):
#   jdbc:mysql://${{MySQL.MYSQLHOST}}:${{MySQL.MYSQLPORT}}/${{MySQL.MYSQLDATABASE}}?useSSL=false&allowPublicKeyRetrieval=true&serverTimezone=UTC
#   Public proxy URL from "Connect" tab (if connecting from outside Railway):
#   jdbc:mysql://HOST:PORT/railway?useSSL=true&allowPublicKeyRetrieval=true&serverTimezone=UTC
#
# SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME  →  Reference: MySQL → MYSQLUSER
# SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD  →  Reference: MySQL → MYSQLPASSWORD
#
# --- Option B: paste JDBC URL from Railway "Connect" (public network; egress may apply) ---
#
# SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:mysql://HOST:PORT/railway?useSSL=true&allowPublicKeyRetrieval=true&serverTimezone=UTC
# SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=root
# SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=<from Railway MySQL variables>
#
# --- Other backend variables on Railway ---
#
# APP_JWT_SECRET=<openssl rand -base64 48>
# APP_FRONTEND_BASE_URL=https://YOUR-FRONTEND.up.railway.app
# FILE_UPLOAD_DIR=/app/uploads/course-content
# SERVER_PORT is set automatically by Railway (do not hardcode)
